<TITLE> Rafique honoured by Bengal Tigers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 24 (bdnews24.com)  The Bengal Tigers, country's lone fan club of the Bangladesh national cricket team, Monday accorded a reception to retired cricketer Mohammad Rafique at Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan (BKSP). Left-arm spinner Rafique, who retired from the international cricket after recently concluding the home series against South Africa, was honoured with two crests at the BKSP ground. Rafique is country's lone cricketer who has 100 wickets in both one-day international and Test cricket. Three former Bangladesh skippers Aminul Islam Bulbul, Naimur Rahman Durjoy and Khaled Mahmud Sujan attended the programme. Former director of Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) Jalal Younus, secretary general of BCB game development committee GS Hasan Tamim and Bengal Tigers general secretary Tabarakul Islam Arif were, among others, present. 
